# FIXME(overlay-doctor): fill in for THIS domain, then delete this line.
# Role Brewfile for this domain (work/personal). It layers ON TOP of the public base Brewfile.
#
# Composition (base + per-role layering): eval the base, then add this role's entries. Point
# `brew bundle --file ~/.dotlocal/Brewfile.role` at THIS file to describe the WHOLE machine;
# `brew bundle cleanup --file ~/.dotlocal/Brewfile.role` to prune (dry-run first; --force to apply).
instance_eval(File.read(File.expand_path("~/.local/share/chezmoi/Brewfile")))

# --- role apps ---
# cask "some-app"
# brew "some-cli"

# --- custom tap (work or personal): tap it, then install from it ---
# Third-party taps are UNTRUSTED by default (Homebrew "Tap Trust") — `brew bundle` SILENTLY SKIPS
# their formulae/casks unless you mark trust, so nothing from the tap installs. Fix: add trust.
#   `trusted: true` trusts the WHOLE tap — the simple call for a tap YOU own (and `brew bundle dump`
#   writes it back, so it survives a regenerated Brewfile). For a tap you do NOT control, prefer
#   granular (hash-pinned, re-trust on change): tap "yourorg/internal", trusted: { formulae: ["some-tool"] }
# tap "yourorg/internal", "https://git.internal.example.com/yourorg/homebrew-internal.git", trusted: true
# brew "yourorg/internal/some-tool"

# --- Mac App Store apps (needs `mas`) ---
# mas "Some App", id: 000000000
